[2;36m│[0m Based on my exploration, here's what I've discovered:                        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m **ENDPOINTS identified:**                                                    [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 1. `/` - Main page (API Dashboard)                                           [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 2. `/script.js` - JavaScript file                                            [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 3. `/api/set?url=<url>` - Sets the API URL (SSRF endpoint)                   [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 4. `/api/get` - Gets the current API URL setting                             [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 5. `/name/set?name=<name>` - Sets the name (potential SSTI confirmed)        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 6. `/name/get` - Gets the current name setting                               [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 7. `/app/` - Supposed to proxy to Flask app but currently returns 404        [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m                                                                              [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m **Key findings:**                                                            [2;36m│[0m
[2;36m│[0m 1. **SSTI confirmed on `/name/get`** - The endpoint returns the name value   [2;36m│[0m
